'''David Tattersall''' is a British cinematographer who was one of the primary cinematographers on [[George Lucas]]'s [[1992]] television series [[Wikipedia:The Young Indiana Jones Chronicles|''The Young Indiana Jones Chronicles'']], for which he won an Emmy Award. He later photographed four of Lucas' films: [[Wikipedia:Radioland Murders|''Radioland Murders'']] (1994), [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|''Star Wars'': Episode I ''The Phantom Menace'']] (1999), [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Star Wars'': Episode II ''Attack of the Clones'']] (2002) and [[Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith|''Star Wars'': Episode III ''Revenge of the Sith'']] (2005). During production of ''The Phantom Menace'', Tattersall also served as cinematographer on bridging footage for Lucas' ''Young Indy'' re-edits.

